g%20an%20opaque%20system%20filled%20with%20twists%20and%20turns.%20It%20doesn't%20help%20that%2C%20until%20recently%2C%20many%20New%20Yorkers%20didn't%20even%20know%20they%20could%20access%20these%20records%20%E2%80%94%20or%20that%20their%20landlords%20might%20have%20been%20overcharging%20them.%20Danielle%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20only%20learned%20that%20she%20could%20request%20her%20rental%20history%20from%20a%20colleague%20who%20had%20worked%20in%20tenant%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20already%20didn't%20kind%20of%20trust%20landlords%2C%20but%20I%20guess%20I%20had%20lived%20in%20this%20world%20where%20I%20assumed%20that%20people%2C%20for%20the%20most%20part%2C%20told%20the%20truth%20about%20stuff%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20adding%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20just%20walked%20away%20with%20just%20a%20complete%20disgust%20of%20anyone%20who%20is%20a%20professional%20landlord%2C%20at%20least%20in%20New%20York%20City.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20TikTok%20becomes%20the%20new%20town%20square%20for%20all%20things%20economic%20transparency%2C%20the%20latest%20target%20of%20populist%20ire%20is%20New%20York%20City%20landlords.%20Several%20videos%20that%20have%20recently%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40openigloo_nyc%2Fvideo%2F7325842918235786538%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egone%20viral%3C%2Fa%3E%20show%20viewers%20how%20to%20look%20into%20their%20rent%20histories%20and%20call%20out%20examples%20of%20potentially%20illegal%20hikes.%20But%20for%20the%20renters%20newly%20discovering%20their%20rights%2C%20it's%20not%20all%20smooth%20sailing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20just%20not%20enough%20resources%2C%20I%20think%2C%20for%20people%20who%20don't%20have%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20to%20spend%20on%20lawyers'%20fees%20to%20be%20able%20to%20advocate%20for%20themselves%20to%20stay%20in%20apartments%2C%26quot%3B%20Danielle%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhen%20TikTok%20found%20the%20renters%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20years%2C%20snagging%20a%20rent-stabilized%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnyc-rent-laws-are-insanely-confusing--we-cleared-them-up-2015-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunit%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20New%20York%20City%20has%20been%20something%20of%20a%20holy%20grail.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20recently%2C%20rent%20stabilization%20was%20in%20the%20spotlight%20after%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Flegal%2Fus-supreme-court-wont-hear-challenge-rent-stabilization-laws-2024-02-20%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20Supreme%20Court%20declined%20to%20hear%20a%20case%20by%20landlords%20to%20weaken%20regulations%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Meanwhile%2C%20New%20Yorkers%20are%20eager%20to%20learn%20if%20they're%20overpaying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAllia%20Mohamed%20was%20inspired%20to%20start%20a%20listings%20and%20landlord%20review%20platform%20called%20openigloo%2C%20in%202020%20after%20struggling%20to%20find%20her%20own%20New%20York%20City%20apartment.%20She's%20posted%20a%20series%20of%20viral%20videos%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40openigloo_nyc%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eon%20TikTok%3C%2Fa%3E%20advising%20renters%20on%20how%20to%20obtain%20their%20rent%20history%20and%20determine%20if%20their%20unit%20is%20rent-stabilized.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20group%20has%20been%20helping%20tenants%20decipher%20the%20documents%20they%20get%20from%20the%20Division%20of%20Housing%20and%20Community%20Renewal%2C%20which%20are%20often%20confusing%20and%20difficult%20to%20understand.%20Mohamed%20said%20she%20thinks%20tenants%20are%20being%20overcharged%20in%20about%205%25%20of%20cases%20based%20on%20the%20rental%20histories%20openigloo%20has%20seen.%20They've%20also%20found%20errors%20or%20missing%20information%20in%20about%2050%25%20of%20rent%20history%20reports.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20more%20information%20that%20tenants%20have%2C%20the%20more%20informed%20decisions%20that%20they%20can%20make%20about%20their%20housing%2C%26quot%3B%20Mohamed%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20videos%20are%20resonating%3A%20An%20influx%20of%20social%20media%20users%20has%20led%20to%20an%20%26quot%3Bunprecedented%26quot%3B%20surge%20in%20rent%20history%20requests%20to%20the%20New%20York%20State%20government%20department%20that%20handles%20housing%20issues%2C%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnyc-apartments-rent-history-stabilized-renters-landlords-overwhelm-government-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBI%20previously%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Wait%20times%20for%20rent%20histories%20are%20now%20at%2020%20business%20days%2C%20up%20from%2010%20in%20late%20January%2C%20as%20a%20result%20of%20%26quot%3Bsocial%20media%20activity.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20renter%20in%20Washington%20Heights%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0whose%20identity%20is%20known%20to%20Business%20Insider%20but%20who%20requested%20anonymity%20for%20fear%20of%20professional%20repercussions%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0said%20he%20was%20inspired%20to%20request%20his%20apartment's%20rent%20history%20earlier%20this%20year%20after%20his%20boyfriend%20sent%20him%20a%20TikTok%20video%20explaining%20how%20to%20do%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20history%20revealed%20that%20his%20unit%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0a%20%242%2C395%20two-bedroom%20that%20he%20shares%20with%20a%20roommate%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0was%20rented%20for%20%24885%20in%202018.%20When%20that%20tenant%20left%2C%20the%20rent%20spiked.%20The%20tenant%20called%20DHCR%2C%20and%20an%20employee%20recommended%20that%20he%20file%20a%20complaint%2C%20which%20he%20did%20just%20a%20few%20days%20later.%20He%20doesn't%20know%20if%20he's%20been%20illegally%20overcharged%20or%20if%20he'll%20end%20up%20seeing%20any%20financial%20benefit%2C%20but%20he%20views%20filing%20a%20claim%20as%20a%20win-win.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20worst-case%20scenario%2C%20nothing%20bad%20happens%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20in%20the%20best-case%20scenario%2C%20you%20know%2C%20it%20could%20really%20be%20life-changing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Carla%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0whose%20last%20name%20is%20known%20to%20BI%20but%20withheld%20for%20privacy%20reasons%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0found%20a%20two-bedroom%2C%20rent-stabilized%20Lower%20East%20Side%20apartment%20on%20Craigslist%20for%20%241%2C850%20a%20month%2C%20she%20knew%20it%20was%20a%20steal%20for%20the%20trendy%20Manhattan%20neighborhood.%20Luckily%2C%20she%20was%20the%20first%20person%20to%20see%20the%20apartment%20and%20apply%20for%20it%2C%20so%20she%20quickly%20signed%20the%20lease%20and%20moved%20in%20in%20December%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20most%20new%20New%20Yorkers%2C%20the%2028-year-old%20had%20some%20familiarity%20with%20the%20city's%20rent-stabilization%20program.%20Her%20aunt%20has%20long%20lived%20in%20a%20stabilized%20unit%20in%20Long%20Island%20City%20and%20has%20had%20to%20fight%20her%20landlord%20to%20stay%20there.%20So%20when%20it%20came%20time%20to%20renew%20her%20lease%20last%20fall%2C%20Carla%20decided%20to%20submit%20a%20request%20with%20DHCR%20for%20more%20information%20on%20her%20unit.%20When%20her%20rent%20history%20came%20back%2C%20it%20showed%20that%20the%20tenant%20before%20her%20paid%20just%20%24875%20in%20rent%20and%20her%20apartment's%20rent%20was%20listed%20at%20%241%2C295.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20was%20just%20like%20fireworks%20%E2%80%94%20I%20was%20like%20something%20is%20wrong%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20I%20consulted%20with%20my%20aunt%20about%20it%20and%20I%20called%20the%20DHCR.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20agency%20recommended%20she%20bring%20the%20issue%20to%20her%20landlord%20and%20see%20if%20they%20could%20resolve%20it%20without%20filing%20a%20claim.%20When%20Carla%20presented%20her%20landlord%20with%20the%20apartment's%20rent%20history%2C%20he%20reimbursed%20her%20about%20%245%2C500%20for%20the%20year%20of%20overcharged%20rent%20and%20lowered%20her%20rent%20to%20%241%2C468%20per%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20former%20social%20media%20content%20strategist%2C%20Carla%20was%20quick%20to%20post%20about%20her%20victory%20on%20her%20TikTok%20account.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40thanks_management%2Fvideo%2F7329984938349038891%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20video%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0which%20used%20a%20clip%20of%20Mohamed's%20video%20advising%20renters%20to%20use%20DHCR's%20resources%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0went%20viral%20with%20nearly%20500%2C000%20likes.%20She%20got%20so%20many%20comments%20and%20direct%20messages%20that%20she%20made%20a%20follow-up%20video%20addressing%20the%20most%20common%20questions%20she%20got.%20Carla%20is%20optimistic%20that%20videos%20like%20hers%20are%20making%20a%20difference.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20this%20is%20gonna%20help%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20and%20hopefully%20save%20people%20some%20money%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Apartment%20blocks%20in%20Manhattan%20on%20February%2026%2C%202016%20in%20New%20York.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F650db2aa12dc4f001a17c667%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22853%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECarla%2C%20a%20tenant%20in%20the%20Lower%20East%20Side%20of%20Manhattan%2C%20posted%20a%20viral%20TikTok%20video%20about%20her%20experience%20getting%20%245%2C500%20in%20backpay%20and%20having%20her%20rent%20lowered%20by%20about%20%24400%20a%20month.%20Her%20experience%20investigating%20her%20own%20rent-stabilized%20unit%20is%20inspiring%20others%20to%20do%20the%20same.%3Cp%3EThomas%20Trutschel%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EBut%20for%20some%2C%20relief%20is%20still%20far%20off%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnna%20Klenkar%2C%20a%20real%20estate%20broker%20in%20New%20York%20City%2C%20has%20had%20an%20overcharge%20complaint%20ongoing%20since%202016.%20She%20found%20out%20that%20her%20landlord%20was%20charging%20roughly%20an%20extra%20thousand%20dollars%20a%20month%20for%20many%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20frustrating%20to%20know%20that%20your%20landlord%20is%20continuing%20to%20reap%20those%20financial%20benefits%20of%20being%20part%20of%20that%20system%20when%20they%20weren't%20necessarily%20abiding%20by%20the%20rules%20of%20that%20system%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKlenkar%20has%20made%20TikToks%20about%20her%20old%20apartment%20and%20rent%20histories%20and%20has%20had%20%26quot%3Blots%26quot%3B%20of%20people%20reach%20out%20with%20their%20own%20rent%20histories.%20She's%20even%20helped%20some%20put%20together%20their%20own%20complaints.%20But%2C%20like%20her%20own%20situation%2C%20that%20doesn't%20mean%20they've%20been%20resolved%20quickly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20seen%20people%20get%20overcharges%20dealt%20with%20pretty%20quickly%2C%20but%20that%20is%20much%20rarer.%20A%20lot%20of%20times%20they%20get%20dragged%20out%20for%20years%20and%20years%20and%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20of%202022%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgothamist.com%2Fnews%2Fovercharged-for-your-rent-in-a-ny-regulated-building-theres-a-backlog-of-3400-complaints%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGothamist%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20DHCR%20had%20a%20backlog%20of%203%2C400%20complaints.%20The%20agency%20reports%20that%20in%20the%20fiscal%20year%202022-23%2C%20it%20processed%20818%20overcharge%20complaints%2C%20up%20from%20326%20in%202020-21.%20Similarly%2C%20the%20count%20of%20overcharge%20orders%20granted%20nearly%20tripled%20over%20the%20same%20time%20period.%20More%20may%20be%20on%20their%20way%20as%20New%20Yorkers%20seem%20to%20be%20requesting%20their%20rent%20histories%20en%20masse.%20Over%20the%20last%20five%20years%2C%20the%20Office%20of%20Rent%20Administration%20has%20won%20back%20nearly%20%2413.2%20million%20in%20rent%20overcharges%20on%20behalf%20of%20tenants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Office%20of%20Rent%20Administration%2C%20within%20New%20York%20State%20Homes%20and%20Community%20Renewal%2C%20continues%20to%20ensure%20the%20laws%20governing%20rent%20regulation%20are%20properly%20administered%20and%20enforced%3B%20that%20includes%20proactive%20audits%2C%20investigations%2C%20and%20other%20enforcement%20activities%20to%20protect%20more%20than%20one%20million%20tenants%20and%20New%20York's%20rent%20regulated%20housing%20stock%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20HCR%20spokesperson%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20to%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2Fnq968%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Rent%20overcharge%20complaints%20processed%20and%20granted%20in%20New%20York%20state%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22317%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EOpenigloo%20is%20working%20on%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.openigloo.com%2Fblogs%2Fnycs-first-rent-stabilization-map%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epublicly%20accessible%20map%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20rent-stabilized%20apartments%20across%20New%20York%20City.%20Because%20only%20the%20tenant%20or%20landlord%20of%20a%20particular%20unit%20can%20request%20rent%20history%20or%20ask%20DHCR%20to%20determine%20if%20a%20unit%20is%20rent%20stabilized%2C%20openigloo%20is%20asking%20tenants%20to%20share%20their%20rental%20histories%20with%20the%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20huge%20frustration%20for%20me%2C%20and%20this%20is%20just%20a%20sort%20of%20a%20broader%20policy%20discussion%2C%20is%20why%20is%20it%20on%20the%20onus%20of%20tenants%20who%20are%20not%20well-versed%20or%20educated%20in%20this%20area%20to%20actually%20enforce%20these%20laws%20on%20their%20behalf%3F%26quot%3B%20Mohamed%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEsteban%20Gir%C3%B3n%2C%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Crown%20Heights%20Tenant%20Union%20and%20the%20Tenants%20PAC%20Board%20of%20Directors%2C%20echoed%20that%20frustration%20around%20a%20system%20he%20viewed%20as%20favoring%20landlords.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20why%20also%20that%20nothing%20is%20proactive%20when%20you're%20dealing%20with%20rent%20stabilization%20%E2%80%94%20the%20tenant%20has%20to%20basically%20initiate%20everything%2C%20even%20if%20it's%20something%20blatantly%20not%20legal%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDanielle%2C%20who%20ended%20up%20getting%20%24150%2C000%20in%20her%20settlement%2C%20said%20that%20she%20had%20difficulty%20parsing%20out%20what%20her%20housing%20documents%20meant%20even%20though%20she%20holds%20multiple%20post-graduate%20degrees.%20She%20imagines%20that%20it's%20only%20worse%20for%20people%20who%20may%20not%20speak%20English%20or%20don't%20have%20the%20time%20and%20resources%20to%20parse%20out%20the%20documents%20or%20find%20a%20lawyer%20who%20can.%20She%20said%20that%20they%20were%20%26quot%3Bexceptionally%20lucky%26quot%3B%20with%20how%20everything%20turned%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20her%20overcharge%20case%20has%20meant%20more%20than%20clawing%20back%20money%20she%20shouldn't%20have%20paid.%20It's%20also%20changed%20her%20life.%20The%20money%2C%20and%20the%20apartment%20they%20were%20able%20to%20buy%20with%20it%2C%20%26quot%3Bhas%20acted%20as%20a%20buffer%20for%20really%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20last%20decade%20of%20my%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20huge%20difference%20between%20getting%20your%20foot%20in%20the%20door%20in%20terms%20of%20being%20a%20property%20owner%2C%20and%20not%20having%20%24150%2C000%20to%20put%20down%20on%20a%20down%20payment%2C%26quot%3B%20Danielle%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20it%20makes%20all%20the%20difference.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAre%20you%20a%20renter%20who%20found%20out%20you're%20being%20overcharged%2C%20or%20got%20money%20back%3F%20Contact%20these%20reporters%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aerelman%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Eerelman%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3