%20as%20underpaid%20as%20servers%20but%20don't%20get%20the%20benefit%20of%20tips.%20But%20Rafidi%20seemed%20stumped%20on%20how%20to%20solve%20the%20problem%20without%20cutting%20into%20waitstaff's%20pay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHow%20do%20we%20not%20take%20from%20one%20to%20give%20to%20the%20other%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BHow%20do%20we%20please%20everyone%20in%20the%20business%2C%20including%20the%20guests%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Tandy%20Wilson%2C%20a%20chef%20at%20City%20House%20in%20Nashville%2C%20said%20that%20although%20he%20doesn't%20like%20tipping%2C%20he%20doesn't%20see%20how%20it%20will%20ever%20go%20away%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frestaurants-america-eating-out-crisis-your-fault-labor-shortage-tipping-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECorey%20Mintz%20reported%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20restaurants%20are%20experimenting%20with%20removing%20tipping%20by%20raising%20food%20prices%20or%20adding%20service%20charges%20to%20their%20menus.%20But%20he%20also%20noted%20that%20customers%20and%20waitstaff%20may%20be%20wary%20of%20the%20new%20model%2C%20making%20it%20an%20imperfect%20solution%20to%20the%20tipping%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ETipping%20culture%20as%20a%20whole%20has%20been%20under%20scrutiny%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20restaurant%20industry%20isn't%20alone%20in%20reaching%20a%20reckoning%20with%20tipping.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlmost%20daily%2C%20a%20story%20or%20social%20media%20post%20goes%20viral%20about%20someone%20being%20asked%20to%20tip%20for%20a%20service%20they%20didn't%20expect%2C%20like%20a%20bride%20who%20was%20asked%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbride-shocked-asked-to-tip-while-purchasing-wedding-dress-tiktok-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etip%20for%20her%20wedding%20dress%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20a%20client%20who%20was%20presented%20with%20the%20opportunity%20to%20tip%20for%20%3Ca%