%20neutralise%20disability%20so%20that%20a%20differently%20abled%20person%20and%20his%20peers%20stand%20on%20equal%20footing%2C%20which%20is%20the%20%26quot%3Bheart%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20theory%20of%20equal%20opportunity%20and%20the%20Constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20because%20of%20this%20that%20the%20more%20appropriate%20term%20to%20use%20would%20be%20'differently%20abled'%2C%20rather%20than%20'disabled'.%20Persons%20who%20are%20differently%20abled%20are%20as%20able%20as%20any%20of%20us%3B%20however%2C%20as%20their%20ability%20is%20different%2C%20it%20poses%20a%20challenge%20when%20they%20seek%20to%20integrate%20with%20the%20societal%20whole%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20judge%20in%20a%20recent%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPersons%20who%20suffer%20from%20disabilities%2C%20as%20recognised%20by%20the%20RPWD%20Act%2C%20are%20no%20different%20from%20you%20or%20me.%20In%20one%20way%20or%20the%20other%2C%20each%20of%20us%20suffers%20from%20disabilities%2C%20known%20and%20unknown.%20Yet%2C%20we%20all%20have%20to%20function%20as%20a%20cohesive%20human%20whole%2C%26quot%3B%20added%20the%20judge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court's%20observations%20came%20while%20passing%20an%20order%20directing%20the%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20University%20(JNU)%20to%20provide%20facilities%20to%20a%20visually%20impaired%20student%20who%20was%20evicted%20from%20the%20hostel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20order%2C%20the%20court%20said%20once%20the%20difference%20is%20%26quot%3Bneutralised%26quot%3B%2C%20a%20differently%20abled%20individual%20is%20able%20to%20rise%20to%20his%20full%20stature%20and%20invoke%20his%20innate%20talents%20and%20faculties%20to%20their%20fullest%20extent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20such%20a%20situation%2C%20the%20person%20who%20was%20otherwise%20regarded%20as%20'disabled'%20often%20equals%2C%20if%20not%20excels%2C%20his%20more%20redoubtable%20peers%20in%20the%20profession%20that%20he%20pursues.%20Mr%20Rahul%20Bajaj%20(the%20petitioner's%20lawyer%20who%20suffers%20from%20visual%20impairment)%20is%20a%20luminescent%20example%2C%26quot%3B%20observed%20the%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2049-year-old%20petitioner%2C%20Sanjeev%20Kumar%20Mishra%2C%20had%20approached%20the%20high%20court%20against%20his%20eviction%20from%20the%20hostel%20on%20the%20ground%20that%20the%20applicable%20rules%20do%20not%20permit%20hostel%20accommodation%20to%20a%20student%20pursuing%20a%20second%20postgraduate%20course.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20high%20court%2C%20while%20granting%20relief%20to%20the%20petitioner%2C%20said%20it%20was%20truly%20ironic%20that%20JNU%20was%20seeking%20to%20defend%20its%20case%20by%20relying%20on%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20petitioner%20-%20a%20100%20per%20cent%20visually%20challenged%20student%20-%20has%20provided%20a%20residential%20address%2021%20km%20away%20from%20the%20JNU%20campus.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709144220000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2019-07%2Fatt9hsso_court-generic_625x300_27_July_19.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fbetter-to-use-differently-abled-not-disabled-delhi-high-court-5146087%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Persons%20suffering%20from%20disabilities%20are%20%26quot%3Bno%20different%20from%20you%20or%20me%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20more%20appropriate%20term%20to%20use%20for%20them%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Bdifferently%20abled%26quot%3B%20and%20not%20%26quot%3Bdisabled%26quot%3B%2C%20the%20Delhi%20High%20Court%20has%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fbetter-to-use-differently-abled-not-disabled-delhi-high-court-5146087%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fbetter-to-use-