20are%20out%20there.%20They%20just%20need%20to%20see%20the%20light%20of%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMohammed%20does%20a%20big%20service%20to%20potential%20Urdu-English%2FTelugu-English%20translators%20by%20collating%20and%20analysing%20prose%20and%20poetry%20originally%20written%20in%20those%20aforementioned%20regional%20languages.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBe%20it%20Jeelani%20Bano%E2%80%99s%C2%A0%3Cem%3EAiwan-e-Ghazal%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Makhdoom%20Mohiuddin%E2%80%99s%20poetic%20repertoire%20or%20Nelluru%20Keshavaswamy%E2%80%99s%20short%20stories%2C%20this%20whole%20corpus%20of%20literature%20(both%20fiction%20and%20non-fiction)%20outdid%20the%20press%20with%20respect%20to%20genuinely%20describing%20both%20the%20human%20and%20political%20tragedies%20that%20occurred%20during%20and%20after%20the%20police%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESome%20better%20drafts%20of%20history%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETelugu%20stories%20like%C2%A0%3Cem%3EYugantham%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0did%20show%20many%20pro-establishment%20Muslims%20becoming%20Razakars.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20such%20character%2C%20Dilawar%2C%20is%20a%20friend%20of%20a%20Telugu-Hyderabadi%20named%20Swamy.%20Despite%20never%20being%20harmed%20by%20Dilawar%2C%20readers%20get%20to%20see%20how%20the%20pluralistic%20ways%20of%20everyday%20city%20folk%20got%20ruptured%20because%20of%20the%201947%20partition%20and%20subsequent%20police%20action%20down%20South.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20Indian%20military%20merges%20Hyderabad%20into%20a%20newly%20independent%20Union%2C%20Swamy%20feels%20elated%2C%20unlike%20Dilawar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20their%20differing%20political%20views%2C%20their%20friendship%20is%20one%20that%20represents%20the%20synthesis%20of%20linguistic%20and%20cultural%20traditions%20that%20coalesced%20under%20the%20pre-Asaf%20Jahi%20era%20Muslim%20regimes.%20Fearing%20the%20repercussions%20for%20his%20Razakar%20activity%20from%20the%20new%20Indian%20establishment%2C%20Dilawar%20migrates%20to%20Pakistan.%20But%20before%20doing%20so%2C%20he%20leaves%20money%20with%20Swamy%20so%20that%20his%20friend%20may%20give%20it%20to%20the%20people%20who%20he%20victimised%20as%20a%20Razakar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20story%C2%A0%3Cem%3EVimukti%3C%2Fem%3E%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20box%20the%20Hyderabadi%20Muslim%20as%20a%20perpetrator%20or%20a%20victim%20of%20the%201948%20massacres.%20Rather%2C%20he%20is%20a%20reformer%20who%20seeks%20to%20do%20away%20with%20regressive%20traditions%20of%20feudal%20debauchery.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELoath%20to%20the%20treatment%20meted%20out%20to%20domestic%20helpers%20within%20the%20noble%20household%20he%20is%20a%20part%20of%2C%20the%20protagonist%20Sultan%20even%20decides%20to%20marry%20one%20domestic%20worker%20whom%20his%20brother%20impregnates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20stories%20about%20scions%20of%20the%20nobility%20taking%20to%20egalitarian%20leftist%20ideals%20against%20the%20Nizam%E2%80%99s%20establishment%20find%20little%20to%20no%20mention%20in%20popular%20discourse%20about%20the%20circumstances%20in%20which%20Hyderabad%20acceded%20to%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20stress%20how%20fiction%20writers%20were%20more%20adept%20at%20revealing%20what%20happened%20before%2C%20during%20and%20after%20that%20episode%2C%20Mohammed%20supplements%20his%20analysis%20with%20memories%20of%20older%20folks%20who%20lived%20through%20the%20police%20action.%20They%20include%20Vara%20Lakshmi%2C%20the%20wife%20of%20legendary%20Urdu-Telugu%20bilingual%20writer%20Kavi%20Raja%20Murthy%2C%20and%20a%2075-year-old%20by%20the%20name%20of%20Razia%20Hussain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20an%20interview%20with%20another%20elder%2C%20Imam%20Hussain%2C%20reveals%20that%20not%20all%20Muslims%20had%20it%20easy%20in%20a%20land%20ruled%20by%20their%20%E2%80%9Cown%E2%80%9D.%20The%20UPenn%20professor%20quotes%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhat%20about%20ordinary%20and%20poor%20Muslims%20like%20me%3F%20We%20never%20had%20any%20%3Cem%3Ejagir%3C%2Fem%3E%20or%20any%20piece%20of%20land%20or%20even%20enough%20bread%20to%20survive%20the%20day.%20I%20know%20hundreds%20and%20thousands%20of%20Muslim%20families%20living%20in%20utter%20poverty.%20The%20%3Cem%3Eashraf%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3Enawabi%3C%2Fem%3E%20families%20%E2%80%93%20both%20from%20Muslims%20and%20Hindus%20as%20well%20%E2%80%93%20never%20cared%20for%20our%20daily%20basic%20needs%20of%20food%2C%20water%2C%20or%20housing.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJeelani%20Bano%20and%20Dasarathi%20Rangacharya%20also%20brought%20out%20the%20contradictions%20apparent%20throughout%20pre-1948%20Hyderabad.%20Bano%E2%80%99s%20novel%C2%A0%3Cem%3EAiwan-e-Ghazal%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0features%20a%20set%20of%20Muslim%20women%20characters%20from%20various%20strata%20of%20Asaf%20Jahi%20Hyderabad%20navigating%20both%20the%C2%A0%3Cem%3Ezenana%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0of%20the%20patriarchal%20nobility%20and%20the%20forests%20that%20served%20as%20the%20battlefields%20against%20the%20princely%20state%E2%80%99s%20rural%20gentry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENizam-ruled%20Hyderabad%20was%20a%20dominion%20where%20the%20feudal%20oppression%20of%20women%20and%20the%20exploitation%20of%20lower%20castes%20were%20woven%20within%20its%20pluralistic%20fabric.%20Although%20the%20Nizam%20VII%20did%20herald%20in%20many%20infrastructural%20and%20educational%20advancements%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%9CGanga-Jamuna%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9CIsa-Moosi%E2%80%9D%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENorth%20India-centric%20literature%2C%20especially%20the%20work%20of%20Qurratulain%20Hyder%2C%20extols%20its%C2%A0%3Cem%3EGanga-Jamuna%20tehzeeb%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Hyderabad%20too%20has%20something%20similar%2C%20yet%20distinct.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20ensure%20that%20its%20composite%C2%A0%3Cem%3EIsa-Moosi%C2%AD%20%3C%2Fem%3Etehzeeb%C2%A0remained%20intact%20after%201948%2C%20left-leaning%20activists%20and%20litterateurs%20also%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fleft-usher-hyderabad-democratic-era-ballots-bards%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fleft-usher-hyderabad-democratic-era-ballots-bards%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1709124658394000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw10tdb8B3rRcpzUP7kI1WmJ%5C%22%3Edid%20their%20part%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0on%20the%20cultural%20front.%20This%20activism%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20just%20limited%20to%20Urdu%20wordsmiths%2C%20but%20Telugu%20ones%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhether%20those%20contradictory%20facets%20of%20Hyderabad%20were%20written%20about%20in%20what%20is%20today%20considered%20the%20more%20%E2%80%9CHindu%E2%80%9D%20Telugu%20or%20the%20%E2%80%9CMuslim%E2%80%9D%20Urdu%2C%20these%20stories%20need%20to%20be%20(re)told.%20The%20former%20language%20has%20tales%20of%20Muslims%20who%20saw%20a%20lot%20of%20upheaval%20while%20coming%20to%20terms%20with%20a%20new%20setup%20where%20their%20predominant%20sources%20of%20subsistence%2C%20namely%20feudal%20landlordism%20and%20government%20services%2C%20were%20taken%20away%20from%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMohammed%20also%20mentions%20other%20writers%20like%20Dasarathi%20Rangacharya%20who%20represented%20the%20confluence%20of%20languages%2C%20traditions%20and%20religions%20that%20is%20the%20Deccan%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20both%20his%20autobiography%20and%20Telugu%20translations%20of%20Mirza%20Ghalib%E2%80%99s%20Urdu%20poetry%2C%20Rangacharya%20was%20a%20bridge%20between%20his%20mother%20tongue%20Telugu%20and%20Urdu%2C%20which%20he%20grew%20to%20love%20from%20childhood.%20Without%20learning%20the%20latter%20language%20from%20Kayasth%20Hindus%2C%20a%20community%20that%20served%20as%20resourceful%20bureaucrats%2C%20learned%20academics%20and%20powerful%20ministers%20in%20a%20predominantly%20Muslim%20establishment%2C%20he%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20have%20gone%20on%20to%20become%20a%20literary%20icon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMissed%20opportunities%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20has%20been%20done%20by%20Afsar%20Mohammed%20when%20collating%20different%20pieces%20of%20Urdu%20and%20Telugu%20writing%20that%20elaborates%20how%20Hyderabadis%2C%20specifically%20its%20Muslims%2C%20reimagined%20their%20place%20in%20a%20more%20democratic%20India.%20However%2C%20with%20those%20new%20Muslims%20aptly%20being%20represented%20as%20survivors%20rather%20than%20victims%2C%20the%201940s-1960s%20time%20frame%20the%20author%20analyses%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20encompass%20the%20period%20during%20which%20the%20real%20Muslim%20renaissance%20took%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20only%20in%20the%201970s%20%E2%80%93%20with%20the%20oil%20boom%20%E2%80%93%20did%20job%20opportunities%20become%20available%20to%20Hyderabadis%2C%20who%20as%20a%20result%20flocked%20to%20countries%20like%20Saudi%20Arabia.%20As%20they%20did%20in%20real%20life%2C%20Muslims%20economically%20also%20found%20their%20feet%20in%20fictional%20short%20stories%20by%20Sahitya%20Akademi-winning%20Urdu%20writer%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fbaig-ehsas-the-prince-of-stories-from-hyderabad%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fbaig-ehsas-the-prince-of-stories-from-hyderabad%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1709124658394000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw3ihrbfOJh_uiXtYttbOylD%5C%22%3EBaig%20Ehsas%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHow%20that%20money%20from%20the%20Middle%20East%20gave%20way%20to%20new%20dilemmas%20forms%20one%20of%20the%20many%20themes%20prevalent%20throughout%20Ehsas%E2%80%99%20repertoire.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20vein%20of%20films%20that%20depict%20how%20the%20hard%20work%20of%20partition%20refugees%20settled%20in%20North%20India%20earned%20back%20a%20lot%20of%20wealth%20lost%20during%20the%201947%20bloodshed%2C%20the%20short%20story%20%3Cem%3EKhaai%3C%2Fem%3E%20also%20centres%20around%20a%20family%20that%20economically%20revives%20itself%20when%20one%20of%20its%20younger%20members%20migrates%20to%20the%20Gulf%20in%20the%201980s.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20story%20is%20reminiscent%20of%20the%20semi-autobiographical%20novel%C2%A0%3Cem%3EDelhi%3C%2Fem%3E.%20In%20the%20second%20half%2C%20Khushwant%20Singh%20elicits%20how%20his%20family%E2%80%99s%20association%20with%20the%20British%20in%20the%20early%201900s%20enriched%20its%20financial%20standing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSudden%20wealth%20creates%20its%20own%20problems.%20We%20were%20far%20too%20busy%20making%20money%20to%20be%20able%20to%20keep%20our%20eyes%20on%20how%20our%20sons%20spent%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20wrote%20Singh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilar%20realities%20of%20Hyderabadi%20youth%20being%20spoilt%20by%20an%20influx%20of%20Gulf%20money%20their%20parents%20earned%20weren%E2%80%99t%20lost%20upon%20Ehsas%20either.%C2%A0%3Cem%3EAalam-Panaah%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0by%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanchronicle.com%2Flifestyle%2Fbooks-and-art%2F031219%2Fremembering-hyds-prolific-litterateurs.html%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanchronicle.com%2Flifestyle%2Fbooks-and-art%2F031219%2Fremembering-hyds-prolific-litterateurs.html%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1709124658394000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw2SkAdBxw7zzhUzj7HDRx1Y%5C%22%3ERafia%20Manzurulamin%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20another%20Urdu%20novel%20which%20focused%20on%20a%20Muslim%20noble%20family%20that%20for%20the%20most%20part%20shed%20its%20feudal%20hangover%20and%20integrated%20itself%20into%20a%20gradually%20free-market%20tilting%20Indian%20business%20landscape%20of%20the%201980s.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENonetheless%2C%20it%20is%20time%20that%20these%20short%20stories%20and%20novels%20written%20by%20many%20Urdu%20and%20Telugu%20authors%20be%20translated.%20If%20not%20that%2C%20they%20should%20at%20least%20inspire%20more%20art%20that%20shows%20how%20the%20Hindu%20Punjabi%20%E2%80%9CPartition%20Refugee%20Family%E2%80%9D%20isn%E2%80%99t%20too%20different%20from%20the%20Muslim%20%E2%80%9CPolice%20Action%20Family%E2%80%9D